{{infobox book | name = CASUAL PEEPS AT SOPHIA | title_orig = Casual peeps at Sophia | translator = | image =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:Casual peeps at sophia.jpg|195px]] --> | image_caption= Lay out of Casual peeps at sophia | author = [[Allama Imdad Ali Imam Ali Kazi]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Sindh]], [[Pakistan]] | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject =[[Philosophy]], [[Religion]], [[Art]], [[History]], [[Poetry]] | genre = [[Prose]] | publisher =[[Sindhi Adabi Board]] | pub_date =1967 | media_type = | pages =194 | isbn = | oclc = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''Casual peeps at Sophia''' is a collection of [[Essays]] and [[Public speaking|Addresses]] by [[Allama I I Kazi]]. The subjects dealt within these essays and addresses cover a wide range of topics such as [[philosophy]], [[religion]], [[history]], [[poetry]], [[art]] and [[literary criticism]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://https//catalog.hathitrust.org/Record/001906147|title=Casual peeps at Sophia|last=Kazi|first=I. I.|date=1967-01-01|publisher=Sindhi Adabi Board|location=Hyderabad, Pakistan}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books/about/Casual_Peeps_at_Sophia.html?id=ZyEgAAAAMAAJ&redir_esc=y|title=Casual Peeps at Sophia|last=Kazi|first=I. I.|date=1967-01-01|publisher=Sindhi Adabi Board|language=en}}</ref>
