'''Elizabeth Gray''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[radio broadcaster]], who has been a [[Radio personality|host]] and documentary producer for [[CBC Radio One|CBC Radio]].<ref name=hume1985>{{cite news |title=Elizabeth Gray back with CBC as producer |author=Hume, Christopher |url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/thestar/access/474658221.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Oct+17%2C+1985&author=Christopher+Hume+Toronto+Star&pub=Toronto+Star&desc=Elizabeth+Gray+back+with+CBC+as+producer&pqatl=google |newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] |date=17 October 1985 |accessdate=21 December 2010}}</ref>

Previously a researcher on ''[[Cross-Country Checkup]]''<ref name=cbcccc>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbc.ca/checkup/history/ |title=History: The Birth of Cross Country Checkup |author=Simon, Andrew |date=4 November 2007 |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation|CBC]] |accessdate=21 December 2010}}</ref> and a substitute host on ''[[This Country in the Morning]]'' and ''[[Morningside (radio program)|Morningside]]'', Gray took over from [[Barbara Frum]] as cohost of ''[[As It Happens]]'' in 1981.<ref name=slotek1981>{{cite news |title=Elizabeth Gray lands her dream job |author=Slotek, Jim |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=YKMyAAAAIBAJ&sjid=2O4FAAAAIBAJ&pg=4355,297449&dq=elizabeth-gray+john-gray&hl=en |newspaper=[[Ottawa Citizen]] |date=2 November 1981 |accessdate=21 December 2010}}</ref>

In a controversial decision by the show's producers, she was replaced by [[Dennis Trudeau]] in 1985. She subsequently hosted ''[[Sunday Morning (radio program)|Sunday Morning]]'' for several years, and produced documentary reports for the network. More recently, with different producers in charge of ''As It Happens'', Gray has returned to the program as an occasional guest host.{{citation needed|date=December 2010}}

She is married to journalist [[John Gray (Canadian author)|John Gray]].<ref name=slotek1981/>

